<h2 id="subject-to-contract">1. Subject to contract</h2>
<p>Every figure you submit, every approval you give, and any convergence between the parties' figures occurs <strong>strictly subject to contract</strong>.</p>
<ol>
  <li>No figure submitted through the Platform constitutes an offer capable of acceptance.</li>
  <li>No approval constitutes acceptance of any offer.</li>
  <li>Convergence does not of itself give rise to any agreement, compromise, or concluded settlement between the parties.</li>
  <li>Nothing said, submitted, displayed or done on the Platform before the Settlement Agreement is executed creates legal relations between the parties in respect of the underlying dispute.</li>
  <li>No party may assert, in any proceedings or otherwise, that a binding settlement arose at any point before execution of the Settlement Agreement.</li>
</ol>
<p>A binding settlement arises <strong>only</strong> on execution of the Settlement Agreement by both parties, and not before.</p>
<p>All figures, approvals and communications made through the Platform are made on a <strong>without prejudice</strong> basis and are inadmissible in any proceedings, save for the purpose of establishing the existence and terms of an executed Settlement Agreement, or of enforcing MidBid's rights under clauses 3 to 7.</p>

<h2 id="not-a-party">2. MidBid is not a party</h2>
<p>MidBid is not a party to the Settlement Agreement and assumes no obligation or liability under it. MidBid does not act as agent, adviser or representative for either party, does not provide legal advice, and does not hold or receive the settlement sum.</p>
<p>Each party is strongly recommended to obtain independent legal advice before executing the Settlement Agreement.</p>

<h2 id="condition-precedent">3. Condition precedent to release of the Settlement Agreement</h2>
<p><strong>Payment in full of the Service Charge is a condition precedent to MidBid's obligation to release the Settlement Agreement for execution.</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Until that condition is satisfied, MidBid is under no obligation to generate, release, transmit or make available the Settlement Agreement in any form, including any preview, draft or downloadable version.</li>
  <li>MidBid's exercise of its rights under this clause is not a breach of any obligation owed to either party. Neither party shall have any claim against MidBid arising from delay in settlement, loss of opportunity, or continuation of the underlying dispute occasioned by non-payment of the Service Charge.</li>
  <li>If the Service Charge is not paid in full within <strong>30 days</strong> of convergence and approval, MidBid may close the matter, and any figures, approvals and convergence shall lapse and be of no effect.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="service-charge">4. The Service Charge</h2>
<ol>
  <li>The Service Charge is calculated in accordance with the published <a href="/fees">Fee Schedule</a>.</li>
  <li>The Service Charge is payable <strong>in equal shares (50/50)</strong> by each party, save where a party elects to cover it in full, or where clause 5 applies.</li>
  <li>The Service Charge becomes due and payable immediately upon convergence and approval by both parties. <strong>It is payable irrespective of whether the Settlement Agreement is subsequently executed.</strong> It is consideration for the mediation process, which has by that point been delivered, and not for the document.</li>
  <li><strong>The activation fee paid to open the case is credited in full against the Service Charge.</strong> The credit reduces the total sum payable, and not the share of the party who paid it, so that each party's half remains equal.</li>
  <li>The Service Charge is not refundable, including where the other party declines to execute the Settlement Agreement.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="joint-and-several">5. Joint and several liability, and substitution</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Each party is <strong>jointly and severally liable</strong> to MidBid for the whole of the Service Charge, notwithstanding the equal-shares apportionment at clause 4.2.</li>
  <li>The apportionment at clause 4.2 governs the position <strong>as between the parties only</strong> and does not limit MidBid's right to recover the whole of the Service Charge from either party.</li>
  <li>Where one party fails to pay its share, the other party may pay the outstanding balance in order to release the Settlement Agreement. This is a right, not an obligation.</li>
  <li>A party who pays more than its share under clause 5.3 is entitled to recover the excess from the defaulting party as a debt, and may require that sum to be recorded in the Settlement Agreement as an additional amount payable by that party.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="authorisation">6. Payment authorisation</h2>
<ol>
  <li>On activation, each party authorises MidBid and its payment processor to store its payment method and to charge it, without further authorisation, for that party's share of the Service Charge on the date it falls due, and for any further sum that party elects to pay under clause 5.3.</li>
  <li>MidBid will notify each party by email before charging under clause 6.1, save where the party confirms the charge on the Platform, in which case the charge may be taken immediately.</li>
  <li>Each party warrants that it is authorised to give this authorisation in respect of the payment method supplied.</li>
  <li>This authorisation remains in force until the earlier of (a) discharge of all sums due to MidBid, and (b) 12 months from activation.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="outside-platform">7. Settlement outside the Platform</h2>
<ol>
  <li>The Service Charge is payable where the parties settle the underlying dispute at any time within <strong>90 days</strong> of convergence, whether or not that settlement is reached through the Platform, recorded in the Settlement Agreement, or at the converged figure.</li>
  <li>Where the sum actually agreed is not disclosed to MidBid, the converged figure applies for the purposes of clause 4.1.</li>
  <li>Each party shall notify MidBid within 7 days of settling the underlying dispute other than through the Platform.</li>
  <li>This clause does not apply where no convergence occurred.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="late-payment">8. Late payment</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Where both parties are acting in the course of a business, MidBid is entitled to interest and fixed sum compensation under the <strong>Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998</strong>.</li>
  <li>In any other case, MidBid may charge interest on overdue sums at 4% per annum above the Bank of England base rate, accruing daily from the due date until payment, both before and after judgment.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="consumers">9. Consumers</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Where a party is a consumer, that party has the right to cancel within 14 days of activation under the <strong>Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional Charges) Regulations 2013</strong>.</li>
  <li>By opening a case and paying the activation fee, a consumer expressly requests that MidBid begin supplying the service during the cancellation period, and acknowledges that the right to cancel is lost once the service has been fully performed.</li>
  <li>Nothing in these terms affects a consumer's statutory rights.</li>
</ol>
